cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques for ground-penetrating radar (GPR) target detection and classification, specifically for the case of abandoned anti-personnel landmines. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of dictionary learning (DL) methods for feature extraction, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR).
